  "riddle": "1. Seek the page that honors those recognized with insignia and awards in the Land of Unexpected Treasures. Discover who is the granter of these prestigious accolades.\n\n2. Imagine standing in the heart of this sultanate. Ascertain how lofty the ground lies beneath the feet of its regal leader.\n\n3. Travelers often rate their experiences. Determine how they have appraised their visits to the ruling seat of this sultanate.\n\n4. Now, blend the height found in clue 2 with the admiration rating from clue 3 to find the difference between 65 and 4.\n\n5. In a land once central to revolutions and known for its baguettes, how high is the land there, taken in meters?\n\n6. A nation under a notorious regime from long past—uncover how many years this state endured.\n\n7. Within the notorious paramilitary chapters of history's dark times, how many divisions were formed at their strongest?\n\n8. Transform the divisions' count: be intrigued by how many 1s appear when the number is dressed in binary.\n\n9. An artist of strings, born in 1938, is linked with musical mastery from India's rich cultural tapestry. Note her arrival year.\n\n10. For the final key, seize the results from clue 4, merge them using (clue 4 + clue 6 + clue 7), and apply the modulus of 10 to reveal a single digit ending your journey through history's echoes.",
